content: On July 11, 1966, the Milwaukee Braves faced the Philadelphia Phillies in a memorable game where pitcher Denny Lemaster threw a remarkable one-hitter, leading the Braves to a 3-0 victory. The only hit given up by Lemaster came in the sixth inning, showcasing his dominance on the mound. This performance not only highlighted Lemaster's talent but also solidified the Braves' competitive edge during the 1966 season.
